---
title: Rockfish Piccata with Sautéed Spinach, Israeli Couscous, and Lemon Caper Sauce
description: Piccata is a simple yet elegant cooking style where meat or fish is sautéed and served with a lemon, caper, herb, and butter sauce. Although piccata is traditionally associated with chicken or veal, our chefs opted for rockfish as the star of this dish because it’s mild and flaky but doesn’t fall apart while cooking. Plus, it serves as the perfect counterpart to pearled couscous and spinach.
